cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on machine learning and data analysis, specifically on the problem of clustering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and information theory, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the use of Gaussian mixture models and the focus on clustering suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
